AMENDEDANALYSIS
Thisbill:
I. Prohibits municipalities from placing limits on maximum road length, provided that the
proposedroadwayorextensionfullycomplieswithstatefirecode.
II. Prohibits municipalities from imposing a cap on the number of housing lots on a dead-end
road or street, unless such cap is in compliance with state fire code and National Fire Protection
Association standard 1141, and provided that the proposed lots otherwise comply with current
zoningrestrictionsandrequirements.
III. Requires municipalities to allow the placement of utilities within or along buffer areas, or
wetland buffers or conservation areas of a subdivision or lot by a special exception or conditional use
permit.
IV. Prohibits municipalities from imposing additional restrictions or requirements regarding
buildingorlotsizeforaffectedpropertiesbeforetheeffectivedateoftheact.
